Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Phomen Singh (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Phomen Singh (pictured), an early Indian migrant to New Zealand, sold sweets and chutneys out of a suitcase?

entry.title: Ephelcomenus (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the artiodactyl Ephelcomenus is thought to have been capable of burrowing?

entry.title: Nadezhda Bantle (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that after Nadezhda Bantle was exiled to the Russian North, she oversaw the development of the hospital in Nikolskoye to become the most advanced in its region?

entry.title: Baldwin–Reynolds House (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the design of the Baldwin–Reynolds House, a mansion built for U.S. Supreme Court justice Henry Baldwin, may have been inspired by Andrew Jackson's home?

entry.title: Vincent Marks (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that pathologist Vincent Marks helped reverse the conviction of socialite Claus von Bülow in a case that was adapted for the film Reversal of Fortune?

entry.title: a school for African-American students in Virginia (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that enrollment at a school for African-American students in Virginia grew from 14 pupils to 1,300 in its first ten years?

entry.title: George Daniel (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that George Daniel submitted his band's demos as coursework while in college?

entry.title: Free and Candid Disquisitions (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the only proposal from the 1749 book Free and Candid Disquisitions to be implemented by the Church of England was a prayer "for the ceasing of the distemper" of cattle?
